## üéØ BUDGET MANAGEMENT PRINCIPLES

### 1. 70/15/8/7 Rule
- 70% ‚Üí Direct program delivery (maximizes student impact)
- 15% ‚Üí Operations & administration (keep overhead low)
- 8% ‚Üí Marketing & outreach (growth)
- 7% ‚Üí Contingency & reserves (financial safety)

### 2. Quarterly Reviews
- **Q1:** Assess spending patterns, adjust forecasts
- **Q2:** Mid-year review, consider program adjustments
- **Q3:** Plan for next fiscal year
- **Q4:** Year-end reconciliation, grant reporting

### 3. Monthly Reporting
- Track against budget
- Identify variances >10%
- Update revenue projections
- Report to board/donors

### 4. Capital Planning
- Depreciation tracking for equipment
- Maintenance reserve (2% annual equipment cost)
- Replacement schedule for aging equipment
- Growth capital for new programs

