## üìà FINANCIAL REPORTING

### Stakeholder Reports

#### 1. Board Reports (Quarterly)
- Income statement (revenue vs. expenses)
- Balance sheet (assets, liabilities, equity)
- Budget variance analysis (planned vs. actual)
- Cash flow projections
- Key metrics (burn rate, runway, growth)

#### 2. Donor Reports (Semi-Annual/Annual)
- Program impact summary
- Financial stewardship statement
- Use of funds breakdown (pie chart)
- Student outcomes & testimonials
- Plans for next period

#### 3. Grant Reports (Per grant requirements)
- Detailed expense documentation
- Program outcomes & metrics
- Beneficiary impact
- Financial reconciliation
- Photos/evidence of program delivery

#### 4. IRS/State (Annual)
- Form 990-N (e-postcard) or 990 filing
- State charitable registration renewal
- Annual audit (if revenue > $100k)

